South African liquor traders say the industry cannot survive another long ban on alcohol sales. And they’re pleading with government to lift the current restriction on the 15th of January. eNCA’s Manqoba Mchunu reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South African liquor traders are pleading with government to lift the current restriction on the sale of alcohol on 15 January. They say the industry cannot survive another long ban on alcohol sales.
It is the third time the industry has had to close down due to lockdown. Liquor traders say there could be more job losses. Watch the video above for more details on this story